<br />
So on a personal note, thank you to all the admins on these sites for doing a great job.<br />
<br />
VIII. In Game Support for Newcomers.<br />
<br />
Now I am a bit of an idealist, but here is what I would ask of the mages on this board who are affluent within the game. If you see a low level mage struggling to learn the class/buy his spells/or just simply understand the complexities of the game mechanics, help them out. Spare some gold or plat coins, not a lot but some. Let them know where they should be fighting at their level, or perhaps a neat trick. Scout classes can be cut-throat all they want, but let us “enlightened” mages be more civilized than an ogre or troll. If anyone has questions regarding mages once the game starts /tell moonkic (I don’t know what server, but that will be my name), or if you have any now I will do my best to answer if you email <a href="mailto:moonkic@hotmail.com">moonkic@hotmail.com</a>. Keep in mind I can’t give any more specifics than what is on the internet but I will hunt down the answers for you.<br />
<br />
And I am bound to have missed some information, but I hope this will be helpful to newcomers to MMORPGs, or just the world of Norath.</div>
