		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_369692">Think the race recommendations needs a refresh in light of the latest stats released by SOE. Looking at all the races and ranking them in order of int, agi and then sta on the basis that you want as much power as possible, followed by the best chance of not being hit, followed by as many hps as your feeble casting body can have I've come up with the following recommendations ranked in order of best to worst. <br />
<br />
Erudite<br />
Ratonga<br />
Gnome<br />
Dark Elf/High Elf<br />
Half Elf<br />
Iksar/Human<br />
Froglok<br />
Wood Elf/Halfling<br />
Kerra<br />
Ogre<br />
Troll/Barbarian/Dwarf<br />
<br />
Any of the races down to froglok are good enough to play as a mage just on int alone and you could make a case for playing a wood elf/halfling mage since they have such high agi to make up for a slight loss of int. Interesting. And I wonder how much your starting stats really matter in the end game? I mean in EQ you could easily gimp your stats at the start by not knowing what you were doing, but in the end you could normally max out your primary stats with the right gear. If the same is true in EQ2 then I'll be trying something a little more exotic than an Erudite mage just to be different. Anyone heard whether or not they will have racially capped stats? Guess that could stymie people wanting to play strange race/class options.<br />
<br />
Cheers<br />
Arkanus<br />
65th Arcanist (Fenwe) - Tribunal Server</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
